
What's new in version 0.14:

  Added ->flock method for locking the handle.

  Added PUSH, POP, SHIFT, UNSHIFT, CLEAR, EXTEND,  DELETE and EXISTS methods.

  Handling of negative position argument to 'SPLICE' is now correct.
  Return of SPLICE in scalar context is now correct.

What's new in version 0.13:

  Added binmode() calls in tests to support Win32 etc.

What's new in version 0.12:

  Trivial change to get SEEK_SET from POSIX instead of Fcntl.

What's new in version 0.11:

  Test suite now more portable; added tests for 'recsep' option.

What's new in version 0.10:

  SPLICE method supported.  Many minor changes.

What's new in version 0.02:

  STORESIZE method implements $#array = $n.

What's new in version 0.01:

  This is the initial release.

